    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Type of chordophone with strings and keys, superficially resembling a harpsichord, but functioning like a hurdy-gurdy. The strings are bowed, creating sustained tones, by means of a series of parchment-covered metal wheels that are brought in contact with the strings by pressing the keys. The wheels were powered either by a footpedal or a crank.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
